syllabus:
**\* This is an all-English course (全英語授課).**

\* In the 2020 edition of this course, the theme is "**Messaging in cloud/edge computing systems.**" Throughout the semester, we will learn both the theory and the practice of data communication. In particular, we will

(1) learn the basics of the queueing model and analysis;

(2) learn both Google's gRPC framework and the widely-used MQTT communication protocol;

(3) learn to study scientific research literature.

\* In general, data communication is an essential part of modern computer networks and Internet-of-Things (IoT) systems. The objectives of this course are for each student to

*   gain insight into analyzing data communication systems;
*   have hands-on experience in systems performance evaluation; and
*   engage in recent advances in data communication systems.

\* Details will be updated on the course webpage: [https://wangc86.github.io/courses/](https://wangc86.github.io/courses/)
